  - "[Properties of Simple Molecular Compounds]\r\n\n\u2022Small molecules are compounds
    made up of molecules that contain just a few atoms covalently bonded together\r\n\n\u2022They
    have low melting and boiling points so covalent compounds are usually liquids
    or gases at room temperature\r\n"
  - "\u2022As the molecules increase in size, the melting and boiling points generally
    increase\r\n\n\n\u2022Small molecules have poor electrical conductivity\r\n"
